Lagos – Ogun State Governor Senator Ibikunle Amosun, has  urged  the new Olota of Ota, Prof. Adeyemi Obalanlege to unite his people and  partner  with other traditional rulers in carrying out his  duties in order to attain success. Besides,he appealed  to the people of Ota and Awori to co-operate with the new monarch to make his reign successful Presenting the staff and instrument of office to the new monarch a, the governor explained that  when there is co-operation among the people and the monarch,it would foster  peace, progress and development of the state He promised that  his administration would  strengthen  traditional institutions,  due to its important role in socio-economic development of the society. In his remarks, the Proprietor of Crescent University, Abeokuta, Prince Bola Ajibola  lauded  Obalanlege’s  contributions to the University’s development when he was there as a teacher. Thanking Amosun and other attendees of the event,the monarch  assured them that Awori land would  be taken to our another level during his reign 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 